Kwale county on Tuesday held a peace forum where politicians seeking various elective posts were asked to act responsibly during the campaign period to avoid violence. County commissioner Kutswa Olaka said Kwale is amongthe regions that were recognised for upholding peace in the 2013 election, and should keep up. &ldquo;Despite threats from groups like the Mombasa Republican Council, the area has been peaceful during elections,&rdquo;Olaka said. Land executive Ali Mafimbo, representing Governor Salim Mvurya, asked residents to shun politicians spreading hate speech.County Peace Committee chairperson Sharif Mbwana said candidates should be ready to lose or win, and hence should restrain themselves from violence. Party candidates, senior security officers, peace committee members and religious leaders attended the meeting.